value: Breeds in North America (chiefly in the interior) from southern Alaska, Great Slave Lake, northern Manitoba and James Bay, south to southern Oregon, northern Utah, southern Colorado, North Dakota (formerly to Minnesota, Wisconsin and Michigan) and southern Ontario; a colony near Cape Whittle, north shore of the Gulf of St. Lawrence. Winters from southern British Columbia, Idaho, Montana, the Great Lakes and New England coast, south to southern Mexico, the Gulf coast and Cuba.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Lakes, marshes, rivers, nesting on rocky, grassy and sandy islets, isolated shores, or occasionally in marshes (breeding); seacoasts, bays, estuaries, rivers, lakes, ponds, irrigated and plowed fields, and parks and garbage dumps in urban areas (nonbreeding).
